//All Css Theory

Basic Syntax of css is
   selector {
            property: value;
            anotherProperty: value;
            }
Like- h1{
       color: purple;
       font-size: 56px;
       }
       
      img{
      border-color:red;
      border-width: 3px;
      }
      
 //This is a basic CSS file and we write css code in the head tag of html.
 <!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>About me</title>

	<style type="text/css">
		
		h1 {
			color: purple;
		}

		h4{
			color: red;
		}
		li{
			text-transform: capitalize;
		}
	</style>
</head>
<body>
<h1>About me</h1>

<h4>MY Hobbies</h4>
<ul>
	<li>Playing Guitar</li>
	<li>Cooking</li>
	<li>Singing</li>
</ul>
</body>
</html>   

//Linking CSS With html.
We just have to create two files, one html and another one is CSS. To link css with html we use link tag and and put the name of the css file there.
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>Demo</title>
	<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="ayush.css">
</head>
<body>
	<p>Linking HTML with CSS</p>


</body>
</html>



//Much more about border and backgroud color.

h1{
	background: red;
	color: rgb(0,0,0);
	border-color: purple;
	border-width: 5px;
	border-style: solid;
}

/*Border is used with three atributes color width and style*/ 

/*Or we can use another method for border*/

h1{
    border:8px dashed purple;
}

h4{
	background: #00FF00;
	color: rgb(0,0,255);
}

li{
	background: #025513;
}
body{
	background: url(https://nighthelper.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/nature_waterfall_summer_lake_trees_90400_3840x2160.jpg);
    background-size: cover;
}

//If we wanna change the backgroud color of the body first we have to use the tag body and then background inside it with the atribute url().

//In a list we can use special id to choose particular list in the given number of lists. Unique id in list is used as given

----HTML CODE
<ul>
	<li class="a">
		<input type="checkbox"> Life
	</li>
	<li class="a">
		<input type="checkbox" name=""> School
	</li>
	<li id="special">
		<input type="checkbox" name="">Fun
	</li
	
	>CSS CODE----

#special{
	border:1px dashed red;
	background: green;
}

.a{
	border:3px solid blue ;
	text-decoration: line-through;
}

//We can also use class to particularise something. Its starts with " . " ; a dot.
// Basically if we wanna particularise one item we use id and if we wanna particularise two or three or more items together we will use class. just have to give same class name to every item and use it to modify the properties.



//Selectors: Now talking about some important selectors
1. Star selector- It'll select all the elements on the page. Syntax- * {
                                                                          property: ;
									  }
2. Descendanat Selector- It'll help to select an element inside an element i.e 
   li a { } means all anchor tag inside the li tag.
   
3. Adjacent Selector- It helps to slecelt the tag element after some certain tag like 

  h4 + ul {} , It means all the ul tag after h4 tag.
  
4. Attribute Selector- We can select many element with the same attribute.By using []. 
For eg. a[href:"http://www.google.com"] {
                             backgroud: blue;
			     }
    eg:   input[type="text"] {
	background: blue;
	}
	
5. Nth of types selector: If we want to select an element particularly inside an element like in a number of lists we have to select a particular list we'll use this selector.
 li: nth-of -type(3) {
      background: purple;
         }
	 
 li: nth-of -type(even) {
      background: purple;
         }

//Talking about specificity, in the css specificity goes as in increasing order given below
First type selectors: li{}
li a{}
li+a{}
Then class atrribute selectors
.class{}
then
input[type="text"] {}

Then the superior one is
ID Selector
#ID for which we first assign ID to someone then write #ayush {
                            backgroud:green;
			    }
//For selectors: https://code.tutsplus.com/tutorials/the-30-css-selectors-you-must-memorize--net-16048 

//Some selectors for the link
1.  X[title]	
    a[title] {
      color: green;
      }
2. X[href="foo"]
   a[href="http://net.tutsplus.com"] {
  color: #1f6053; /* nettuts green */
}

3. X[href*="nettuts"]
  a[href*="tuts"] {
  color: #1f6053; /* nettuts green */
}

4. X[href^="http"]
   a[href^="http"] {
   background: url(path/to/external/icon.png) no-repeat;
   padding-left: 10px;
  }
5. X[href$=".jpg"]
   a[href$=".jpg"] {
   color: red;
}

["^" -> It's for the beginning and "$" for the end.]

//Code to aplly shadows on css
HTML Code-
<div class="z">
	<img src="ayush.jpg"  >
    </div>
    
CSS Code-

body{
				width: 500px;
				margin: 50px auto;
				position: relative;
			}

.z {
			-webkit-box-shadow: 10px 10px 10px rgba(0,255,0,0.5);  //Main function used to implement shadows.
			-moz-box-shadow: 10px 10px 10px rgba(0,255,0,0.5);    //we use this code so that this shadow thing will
			box-shadow: 10px 10px 10px rgba(0,255,0,0.5);           work on mozzila and elsewehere.
			padding: 10px; 
			background: white;
			
		}

.z img {
	max-width: 100%;
	border: 2px inset blue; 
}


.z:after {
   content: " ";
   -webkit-box-shadow:10px 10px 10px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
   -moz-box-shadow:10px 10px 10px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
   box-shadow:10px 10px 10px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
   position: absolute; 
   width: 30%;
   bottom: 20px;
   right: 90px;
   height:40px;
   z-index: -1; /*it'll put the shadow backword*/
   -webkit-transform: skew(-70deg);
   -moz-transform: skew(-70deg);
   transform: skew(-70deg);
}

//Sometinng more about font-
font-family: We use to set font type like arial.
font-size: To set the size of the font.
font-weight- To set the boldness of the font. It goes from 100 to 800. 100 is the least bold and 800 is the boldest.
line-height- To maintain the gap between two consecutive lines vertically.It goes like 1, 1.5, 2 ..
text-align- To set the alignment of the text like center
text-decoration- To set some properties like line through or underline.


//Something about margin and padding.
Padding basically area between the border and the inner image.
p{
	border-left: :2px solid blue;
	width: 50%;  
	height: 10%;
    padding: 10px;
    padding-left: 40px;	
    margin-top:100px;
    margin: 20px 40px 500px 100px; /*Top right bottom left*/
    margin: 0 auto 0 auto; /*Top and bottom 0 and left and right auto*/
    margin: 0 auto;/* top and botton 0 and left and right auto*/
    margin: 20px 500px; /*Does the same thing*/
    float:left; //Align everything towards left.
}
